Real estate company, Adron Homes has donated the sum of one hundred Million Naira (N100 million) to Ogun, Lagos, Nassarawa, Oyo state including FCT Abuja to support the government as relief funds during this coronavirus pandemic in Nigeria. According to the director of public affairs Southwest, Barrister Kemi Osude-Laniyan who spoke to our correspondent, she said Adron Homes is known with the spirit of giving, supporting the traditional talents since inception. The breakdown of the 100million to curb the spread of COVID 19 includes N20 million to Lagos government,
N20million to Ogun State government, N20million to Oyo State government, N20million to Nasarawa state government and N20million to FCT Abuja. The donation was done through the office of the director of public affairs Southwest and Honourable Tayo Agbaje, director of public affairs Northern States. Barrister Osude-Laniyan said, ”We at Adron Homes has thought it expedient to donate one hundred million Naira upon the approval from Aare Adetola Emmanuel King, our Chairman to Lagos, Oyo, Ogun, Nassarawa, and Abuja as our corporate social responsibility in supporting the government during this period of Coronavirus outbreak, we also appreciate the government for deeming it necessary to donate relief items to the vulnerable people in the country. We have handed over the funds to the five states through their deputy governors and commissioners”. She advised Nigerians to stay at home during this period, follow government measures to end this coronavirus pandemic by maintaining social distancing, using nose masks, washing their hands at all times with alcohol based sanitizer at all times. Hon Tayo Agbaje noted that the company was saddled with the responsibility of making Nigerians better and that is why they are donating funds to support the Ogun, Oyo, Lagos, Abuja and Nassarawa respectively government.